# 🎨 Drawing App

A simple browser-based drawing application that allows users to sketch freely on a canvas. The project also includes a real-time collaborative version powered by WebSockets, enabling multiple users to draw together in the same room.

---

## 🚀 Live Demo

| Version               | Description                                                                                         | Link                                     |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Frontend Only         | Static version hosted on GitHub Pages. Supports drawing but **no real-time collaboration**.         | https://jaydeep077.github.io/Drawing_app |
| Collaborative Version | Full application hosted on Render with a **Node.js WebSocket server** for real-time shared drawing. | https://drawing-app-v2mx.onrender.com    |

---

## ✨ Features

* Freehand drawing on canvas
* Adjustable brush size and color
* Eraser tool
* Text tool for adding notes
* Clear canvas and save drawing as image
* Dark / Light theme toggle
* Real-time collaborative drawing using WebSockets
* Shareable room links for multi-user drawing

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend**

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript
* Canvas API

**Backend**

* Node.js
* WebSocket (`ws`)
* dotenv

---

## 👥 Collaboration

Open the same room link in multiple browsers to draw together.

Example:

https://drawing-app-v2mx.onrender.com/?room=test123

---

## 📦 Installation (Local Development)

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Jaydeep077/Drawing_app.git
cd Drawing_app
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Start the server:

```bash
node server.js
```

Open in browser:

```
http://localhost:3000
```

